<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Henry, Alexander. Travels in the Red River Department (Abridged), 1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0024</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">78</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">August</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">the Trees<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  It is certainly a charming situation &#8212; I remember of no plaine that pleased me more.  Here we stopped for refreshment having killed a fat she Buffaloe we kindled a good fire which in the twinkling of an Eye was surrounded with delicious <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Appolats</span> or Steaks<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  For the rest of the day the plain being almost covered with water we had difficulty to wade through<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  We went slow and our horses were greatly fatigued when we Encamp<span class="AddHand-author">t</span> in the Evening near <span style="text-decoration:underline;">River la Sourie</span> where we could not succeed to make a fire the dung was so damp that heaps of it could produce nothing but a disagreeable smoke<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The flies were Extremely annoying some of our horses broke loose and fled<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  We flew after them but it was so extremely dark that we could not see our own lengths &#8212; afraid of losing our camp we returned and passed the rest of the night very unpleasantly.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday 5<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The whole of this day was lost looking for the horses some of which were excellent racers consequently the owners felt uneasy.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday 6<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">At day break Seven of our party mounted and went in search of the Stray Horses &#8212; while the others were employed to transporting the Baggage to the Banks of the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">River la Sourie</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
